activities:
CDK Global, LLC receives personal information from the EU/EEA and/or Switzerland as both a data processor and a data controller. The purposes for which CDK receives, maintains, and processes personal information depend on the products and services involved. When CDK acts as a data processor for its clients, CDK does not own or control any of the personal information it processes on behalf of its clients. All such personal information is owned and controlled by CDK’s clients.  

CDK receives personal information in the course of the following business activities:

1.	Administering the contractual relationship between CDK and contractors located in the EEA or Switzerland; 
2.	Managing the business and real estate interests of CDK;
3.	Contacting agents and/or contractors regarding business matters;
4.	Effecting leases, purchases, sales or other transactions with businesses or individuals;
5.	Communicating information regarding CDK’s services;
6.	Performing sales and marketing activities as permitted by applicable laws;
7.	Storing and managing information of prospective, current and former clients, suppliers, vendors and partners;
8.	Relationship management;
9.	Managing obligations required by contracts or law, including investigations of each;
10.	Fraud detection and prevention; 
11.	Data processed by the threat management platform and its related technologies and procedures that will provide advanced prevention, detection, response and intelligence capabilities to protect CDK and the client data it processes;
12.	Providing data, website and application hosting and maintenance; 
13.	Providing email, telephone and network connectivity and similar information technology infrastructure and services; 
14.	Monitoring, operating and improving CDK’s online portals, website, offerings and services;  
15.	Authenticating system access or access to online portals or websites; 
16.	Supporting clients’ use of products and services, including by:  addressing client inquiries and requests for service or support; managing issue escalations; and providing remote services, troubleshooting and technical support for relevant systems and databases;
17.	Providing various enhanced or add-on services to which a client has subscribed; 
18.	Training personnel;
19.	Conducting data analytics;
20.	Providing data back-up and restoration; and
21.	Other purposes as disclosed to and consented to by clients.

As a data controller, CDK processes personal information of prospective, current and former employees for human resources activities and employment purposes, including:  

1.	Recruitment and staffing (including the selection and management of CDK’s workforce); 
2.	Administration of compensation and benefit programs (including bonuses and stock plans); 
3.	Time and expense management and other workplace administration; 
4.	Performance management and training, including verification of compliance with CDK policies and procedures; 
5.	Talent management, advancement and succession planning; 
6.	Identity verification and authentication, including system administration and access credentialing; 
7.	Providing advanced prevention, detection, response and intelligence capabilities to protect employee personal data; 
8.	Legal and regulatory compliance, litigation, investigations, and risk management (including systems for storage of legal work products, documents and information); 
9.	Corporate audit, analysis and consolidated reporting;
10.	Information to protect CDK, its workforce, its clients and the public against injury, theft, legal liability, fraud or abuse; 
11.	Other legal and customary business-related information, such as making back-up copies of files for business continuity, as needed for computer system maintenance and other everyday human resource purposes; 
12.	Personal information collected through its internal websites, including without limitation in connection with subscriptions for newsletters, downloads of materials and registration for products and services, including online and offline personal information pertaining to prospective, current and former employees and other human resources data; 
13.	Data processed by the threat management platform and its related technologies and procedures that will provide advanced prevention, detection, response and intelligence capabilities to protect CDK and the employee data it processes;
14.	Employee communications, including hotline reporting systems;
15.	Maintaining a global employee directory and employee headcount; 
16.	Carrying out and supporting  human resources functions and activities, including booking and approval of annual or sick leave and performing employee satisfaction surveys;
17.	Carrying out obligations under employment contracts and employment and benefits laws;
18.	Administering employee participation in human resources plans and programs, including systems for managing, processing, and storing employee forms;
19.	Managing disciplinary and termination matters;
20.	Making business travel arrangements and maintaining travel management systems;
21.	Systems enabling collaboration, including document sharing;
22.	Systems for storage and distribution of internal emails and archiving historical data;
23.	Managing and responding to employee requests for service or support; 
24.	Supporting employees’ use of products and services, including by:  answering employee requests received by a help desk or technical support center, addressing employee inquiries and requests for service or support, managing issue escalations, and providing remote services, troubleshooting and technical support for relevant systems and databases;
25.	Business operations purposes, including maintaining records related to mergers, acquisitions, reorganizations, sales, distributions, dispositions, financial management and reporting; 
26.	Testing, validating and processing data for employee support programs and systems; and
27.	Internal administrative purposes and purposes as disclosed and consented to by employees.
